title: GOP's populist revolt arrives at Capitol, complicating Iran debate
text:
10 GOP's populist revolt arrives at Capitol, complicating Iran debate 
The Washington Post: The anti-establishment disenchantment now roiling the Republican presidential nominating contest landed on Congress’s doorstep Wednesday, with two presidential candidates rallying opposition to the Iran nuclear deal on the Capitol facade, targeting not just President Obama but GOP leaders as well.“We are led by very, very stupid people — very, very stupid people,” front-runner Donald Trump told the crowd, eliciting hearty cheers. “We cannot let it continue.”
